      '\n<li>In celebration of the upcoming holidays, let’s create a small world in your very own crystal ball!</li>\n<li>You can customize your globe from top to bottom, including different bases and background music!</li>\n<li>Accept ‘[Maple Globe] Gaze Into the Crystal Ball!’ quest in the star event notifier on the left side of the screen. Upon completion, you will receive a <strong>Maple Globe</strong> chair.</li>\n<li>You can collect <strong>Crystal Energy</strong> when hunting monsters near your level (20 levels below and 20 levels above).</li>\n<li>You can obtain up to 200 Crystal Energies daily per character.</li>\n<li>When you have enough Crystal Energy, your Maple Globe chair will level up and you\'ll unlock the following customizations! Each level up requires the following amount of Crystal Energies: <br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lv. 2 Tree:</strong> 100 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 3 Chair:</strong> 200 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 4 Mini Figure 1:</strong> 200 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 5 Pose:</strong> 300 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 6 Base:</strong> 300 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 7 Glass:</strong> 400 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 8 Expression:</strong> 400 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 9 Effects:</strong> 500 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 10 Mini Figure 2:</strong> 500 Crystal Energies</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 11 Music:</strong> 500 Crystal Energy</li>\n<li>You must have at least 3 materials registered in your decoration UI from the previous level to level up.<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Ex. In order to level up to Lv. 3, you must have at least 3 Tree materials registered in the UI and 200 Crystal Energies.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Once your chair reaches Lv. 11, you’ll receive the <strong>Maple Globe Owner</strong> medal.</li>\n<li>Once your chair reaches Lv. 11 and you’ve obtained all Rank S materials, you’ll receive the <strong>Maple Globe Collector</strong> medal. The Rank S materials are the following:\n<ul>\n<li>Globe Tree: Elluel Cherry Tree <strong><br></strong></li>\n<li>Globe Tree: Elodin Moonlight Tree <strong><br></strong></li>\n<li>Globe Tree: Arcana Spirit Tree <strong><br></strong></li>\n<li>Globe Chair: Toy Car Chair <strong><br></strong></li>\n<li>Globe Chair: Swing Chair </li>\n<li>Globe Glass: Sparkling Transparent Glass </li>\n<li>Globe Glass: Sparkling Sky Blue Glass </li>\n<li>Globe Glass: Sparkling Dark Glass </li>\n<li>Globe Effect: White Starlight Dust </li>\n<li>Globe Effect: Sprinkling Blue Dust </li>\n<li>Globe Effect: Five-Color Mote of Light </li>\n<li>Globe Effect: Prismatic Light Fragment </li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 1: Lil Lotus </li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 1: Lil Phantom </li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 1: Lil Lucid </li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 2: Lil Orchid </li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 2: Lil Cygnus</li>\n<li>Globe Mini Figure 2: Lil Damien </li>\n<li>Globe Base: Fancy Jewel Base </li>\n<li>Globe Base: Classic Music Box Spring Base </li>\n<li>Globe Base: Classic Elegant Base </li>\n<li>Globe Pose: Fly</li>\n<li>Globe Pose: Ghost </li>\n<li>Globe Music: Way Back Home </li>\n<li>Globe Music: Primrose </li>\n<li>Globe Music: Lake of Oblivion </li>\n<li>Globe Music: Arcana </li>\n<li>Globe Music: Esfera</li>\n<li>Globe Expression: Goo Goo </li>\n<li>Globe Expression: Wink</li>\n<li>Globe Expression: Zzz </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>There are various ways to collect materials to customize your Maple Globe.<br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Condensed Crystal Energy</strong> (Reactors that randomly appear in Lv. 101 - 275 hunting map. You can harvest them 10 times daily per character.)</li>\n<li><strong>Bosses</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Elite Monster/Elite Boss</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Monsters/Certain Content Monsters</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Arcane River Daily Quest</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Monster Park</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Bounty Portals</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dimensional Invasion</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Flag Race</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Hidden Missions</strong></li>\n<li><a href="https://maplestory.nexon.net/news/63875/v-219-awake-flicker-of-light-patch-notes#deco" target="_blank"><strong>[Awake] Decoration Shop</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href="https://maplestory.nexon.net/news/63875/v-219-awake-flicker-of-light-patch-notes#sunny" target="_blank"><strong>Sunny Sunday</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href="https://maplestory.nexon.net/news/63898/update-dec-15-cash-shop-update-for-december-16" target="_blank"><strong>Gachapon</strong></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Maple Globe can only be decorated while your character is in town by accepting the ‘[Maple Globe] Decorating Your Maple Globe’ quest within the star event notifier on the left side of the screen.</li>\n<li>After your chair reaches at least Lv. 3, you can request for your Maple Globe Chair to be displayed as a statue for 1 hour. After your chair was displayed as a statue, you must wait 2 hours in order to request again. You can request up to 3 times daily per character.<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Click Maple Globe Statue Platform located in Henesys, Leafre, and Nameless Town. You will be asked to pay the following amount of mesos as a payment;<br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>1 ~ 15 times:</strong> 100,000,000 mesos</li>\n<li><strong>15 ~ 30 times:</strong> 200,000,000 mesos</li>\n<li><strong>31 and more times:</strong> 300,000,000 mesos</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can interact with other players’ chair statues up to 15 times daily per character. You can only interact with the same player’s chair statue once a day and you cannot interact with your own statue.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>There are also special parts on top of the customizations!<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Complete the following missions to receive a special Maple Leaf effect on your chair:<br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><strong>Center </strong>Leaf</strong><br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lv. 1 Red Autumn Maple Leaf:</strong> Reach Lv. 7 on your chair and obtain all Rank S materials for the customizations you’ve unlocked so far.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 2 Silver Maple Leaf:</strong> Reach Lv. 9 on your chair and obtain all Rank S materials for the customizations you’ve unlocked so far.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 3 Gold Maple Leaf:</strong> Reach Lv. 11 on your chair and obtain all Rank S materials for the customizations you’ve unlocked so far.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong><strong>Left </strong>Leaf</strong><br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lv. 1 Red Autumn Maple Leaf:</strong> Interact with other players’ chair statues 20 times.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 2 Silver Maple Leaf:</strong> Interact with other players’ chair statues 50 times.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 3 Gold Maple Leaf:</strong> Interact with other players’ chair statues 100 times.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Right Leaf</strong><br>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lv. 1 Red Autumn Maple Leaf:</strong> Set up your Maple Globe Chair statue 15 times.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 2 Silver Maple Leaf:</strong> Set up your Maple Globe Chair statue 30 times.</li>\n<li><strong>Lv. 3 Gold Maple Leaf:</strong> Set up your Maple Globe Chair statue 50 times.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>These special parts cannot be removed and will be displayed with the chair permanently.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You will have until <strong>January 8 at 11:59 PM UTC</strong> to finalize your globe customization using the UI even after the event ends.</li>\n<li>Maple Globe can be done per character.</li>\n',
